<HEAD>Bright &amp; Brief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WAYNE, Ind. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A diaper-clad ``<LOCATION>Indiana</LOCATION> Dan'' and his
companion, ``<PERSON>Kennebunk George Bushkin</PERSON>,'' cavort in a coloring book
that takes a cockeyed look at the president and vice president.
   President <PERSON>Bush</PERSON> wears a business suit and has an elephant's nose
and ears in the 48-page book. Vice President <PERSON>Quayle</PERSON> is portrayed as
a chubby baby wearing only a diaper and a golf visor.
   Creator <PERSON>James Travers</PERSON>, a printer and typesetter from <LOCATION>Wilmington</LOCATION>,
<LOCATION>Del.</LOCATION>, said his inspiration was a nagging question after the two
took office: ``Who is <PERSON>Dan Quayle</PERSON>?''
   The book is called ``<LOCATION>Indiana</LOCATION> Dan and His Search for Political
Par Excellence.'' In one part, ``<LOCATION>Indiana</LOCATION> Dan,'' uses a magical golf
putter to play doubles against senators with partner ``Kennebunk
George.'' Before tee-off, <PERSON>Dan</PERSON> must recite the senators' names,
their state capitals, state nicknames and the dates their states
joined the union.
   At the bottom of each page are political quotes from famous
people _ and golf rules and definitions.
   Travers has sold a few hundred copies, at <MONEY>$8.95</MONEY> each, since the
book was published in <DATE>July</DATE>.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>AUBURN, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A diaper-clad ``<LOCATION>Indiana</LOCATION> Dan'' and his
companion, ``<PERSON>Kennebunk George Bushkin</PERSON>,'' cavort in a coloring book
that takes a cockeyed look at the president and vice president.
   President <PERSON>Bush</PERSON> wears a business suit and has an elephant's nose
