<LEADPARA>  BETTE MIDLER; (box) The hottest teaming since Tracy and Hepburn  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  West  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  WEST CLOSE-UPS  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>  Miss M's co-stars have ranged from <PERSON>Nick Nolte</PERSON> to <PERSON>Woody Allen</PERSON>, but she has yet
to achieve the teaming that she dreamed up for Vanity Fair. "I wanted so much
to do a movie with Pee-wee Herman. . . . I wanted to do a 'My Little
Chickadee' type of thing in which he falls in love with me in an innocent way,
and I kind of use him in a nefarious way. Personally, I happen to like
Pee-wee. He's such a sweet guy. . . . I don't know what the hell he was doing
in that theater. I swear to God! But what's the big deal? That's what those
theaters are for. . . . How can you be so hypocritical as to have one in your
community and then pretend you don't know what's going on in them? . . . I saw
something on <PERSON>Joan Rivers</PERSON> that so stunned me I didn't even know what country I
was in. She had a sex therapist on, which was an excuse to talk about
masturbation. How to do it, when to do it. This was daytime TV! It was so low!
. . . And yet they'll put that on television and then crucify Pee-wee <PERSON>Herman</PERSON>
for going into a theater that they have provided for him to go into. This is
my new favorite expression: What a world! What a world!"; <PERSON>JAMES CAAN</PERSON>; (box)
Double-crossed by the Duke; <PERSON>Midler</PERSON>'s "For the Boys" co-star made a big
comeback with "Misery" last year, getting back on track with a Hollywood
career that started in the '60s, when he made <ORGANIZATION>Howard Hawks</ORGANIZATION>' "El Dorado" with
<PERSON>John Wayne</PERSON>. The up-and-coming actor hit it off with the aging superstar, <PERSON>Caan</PERSON>
recalled in Premiere: "I got on pretty well with him. I was about half a stunt
man, all my friends were stunt men, and he liked that kinda stuff. He was . .
. like a 12-year-old kid. One time, I came back to my trailer, and he'd filled
it full of garbage cans. He made me play chess with him, and I beat him the
first time. Last time that happened. He'd cheat. I'd get these phone calls,
you know, and I'd come back and go, 'Hey, that rook wasn't over there.'
'Whaddaya mean, kid? That was right there.' "; <PERSON>JANINE TURNER</PERSON>; (box) Can looks
kill a career?; Before "Northern Exposure," her first exposure was as the
youngest model, at age 15, ever signed by <ORGANIZATION>Wilhelmina Agency</ORGANIZATION>. From there she
moved into acting, with her first big part on the soap "General Hospital." She
was also engaged for a while to another former soap star, <PERSON>Alec Baldwin</PERSON>: "He
was just off 'The Doctors' and I'd just left '<ORGANIZATION>General Hospital</ORGANIZATION>,' " she told
<ORGANIZATION>Redbook</ORGANIZATION>. "His career was taking off and I was struggling, showing up at
bathing-suit auditions where they'd literally ask me to do a 360-degree turn.
I watched him get jobs that were very credible and respectable, and I was
supposed to be the bimbo running down the beach in a bikini. Alec's gorgeous,
but he's a man -- his looks don't detract from his integrity as an actor. I
think, as a woman, you get pigeonholed."; <PERSON>ROBERT MITCHUM</PERSON>; (box) A stickler for
the truth; He has a cameo role in the remake of a film in which he starred,
"Cape Fear." But over his career, he told <ORGANIZATION>Interview</ORGANIZATION>, there were a lot of big
films that he turned down: "I don't believe in conditions being falsified in
order to make a script work. Take 'In the Heat of the <ORGANIZATION>Night</ORGANIZATION>.' Opening scene,
the guy is being thrown out of a saloon in <LOCATION>Mississippi</LOCATION>. But there were no
saloons in <LOCATION>Mississippi</LOCATION>. Another one, 'The Defiant Ones' -- you had a black man
and a white man chained together on a <LOCATION>Florida</LOCATION> chain gang, but it was against
the law. I was on a chain gang in <LOCATION>Georgia</LOCATION>. I know what it's like. I was only
15 years old. I figured, it ain't gonna last forever. I didn't think it was
going to be my course in life. What the hell, I met a lot of interesting
people. People who'd teach you how to burgle."  </TEXT>
